elementList.description: This apartment was recently refurbished, located on the ground floor of a building in the traditional and pleasant neighborhood of Ajuda, in Lisbon.   Located next to Calçada da Ajuda and 300 meters from the Parish of Belém (riverside area), the apartment we propose is close to different points of tourist and cultural interest - the Polo Universitário da Ajuda, the National Palace and the Ajuda Botanical Garden; the Portuguese School of Equestrian Art, the Palace of the Presidency of the Republic, the National Coach Museum, the MAAT, among others, as well as various points of traditional commerce and essential services, such as: Municipal Market, supermarkets, restaurants, pharmacies, etc. In relation to means of transport; a few meters from the house there are bus stops and 1km away is the Belém Train Station (Cais do Sodré - Cascais line). This apartment was recently renovated, with a 35m2 living room with cable TV, a fully equipped kitchen (independent), three closets for clothes and storage (built-in) and a nice patio with 15m2. In total, the house has 80 m2. The kitchen is equipped with an electric stove and oven; microwave and fridge (built-in). It also has small appliances (toaster, coffee machine and kettle). The cylinder and washing machine are located in the storage room. Another asset of the house is the existence of bars on the doors that access the patio. In addition, all windows have double glazing. This house is furnished with some vintage-style wooden furniture, which combined with other contemporary furniture makes it extremely comfortable. Take advantage of the unique opportunity to live in a historic-cultural area, next to the river.. . Value: €1500/month Conditions to rent: Guarantor with Portuguese nationality and 2 months deposit. If you do not have a guarantor, we only accept full advance payment. Visits will be scheduled after the presentation of the IRS and the last 3 pay stubs. 1 year contract. The expenses are not included.
